7. Commit (save) that too

**Now deploy it on Railway (the free internet computer):**

1. Go to **railway.app** → sign up with your GitHub account
2. Click **"New Project"** → **"Deploy from GitHub repo"** → pick `ig-backend`
3. Railway will automatically start running your code — wait ~1 minute
4. Click on your project → go to the **"Variables"** tab → click **"Add Variable"** twice:
   - Variable name: `APP_ID` → value: your App ID from Step 1
   - Variable name: `APP_SECRET` → value: your App Secret from Step 1
5. Click **"Settings"** tab → scroll to **"Networking"** → click **"Generate Domain"**
6. Railway gives you a URL like `ig-backend-production.up.railway.app` — **copy this URL** 🎉

---

## 📱 WORKER 3 — Plugging everything into the app

Now you connect all three workers together. This is the easy part!

1. Open the app I built (scroll up in this chat)
2. In the **Setup screen**, fill in:
   - **Instagram App ID** → paste the App ID from Worker 1
   - **Backend URL** → paste the Railway URL from Worker 2
3. Click **Save & Continue**
4. Click **Continue with Instagram**
5. Instagram opens → log in → tap **Allow**
6. You land back on the app and see your **real live Instagram data** 🎉

---

## 🗺️ The whole thing as a story
```
You click "Connect with Instagram"
        ↓
Instagram says "who are you?" → you log in
        ↓
Instagram gives your app a secret one-time CODE
        ↓
Your app sends that code to YOUR Railway server
        ↓
Railway whispers your App Secret to Instagram
and trades the code for a real ACCESS TOKEN
        ↓
Your app uses that token to ask Instagram:
"Hey, give me this user's posts and profile!"
        ↓
Instagram sends back real data 📊
        ↓
Your beautiful dashboard lights up! 🎉
